Class FlashTank

  • java.lang.Object
    • FlashTank
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable

    public class FlashTank
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.lang.Cloneable
    This class represents a flash distillation vessel and contains three stream objects for the inflow and outflows. Each stream is composed of an array of species. The outlet streams should usually be the same temperature as the flash tank. Notes: When flash tank temp is set, outlet stream temps are also set

      • FlashTank

        public FlashTank(HeatExchanger flashTankHeatExchanger,
                 Stream feedStream,
                 Stream vapourStream,
                 Stream liquidStream,
                 double flashTemp,
                 double pressure)
        Builds a flash tank out of its necessary components.
        Parameters:
        flashTankHeatExchanger - The simple heat exchanger. Used to store the value of Q.
        feedStream - The inlet of the flash tank. Contains known species and compositions.
        vapourStream - The outlet vapour stream. For now it will be empty, but it will be solved in downstream methods.
        liquidStream - The outlet liquid stream. For now it will be empty, but it will be solved in downstream methods.
        flashTemp - The temperature of the flash tank. For case 1 and 3 it is known; for case 2 it will be solved for.
        pressure - The operating pressure of the flash tank
